{"author":{"id":"729f4229091d502775e0e5c4bfc138609955b348584d955f4229a3d76892d2a9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1507645524,"nonce":"NKSh7iu/RI/dDLYHp9HsC6DIoFE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjQyNDg3MTM=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1511","origin":"github"},"title":"STAR with the --limitBAMsortRAM option","message":"It turns out that if you align against a small genome (e.g., dm6), the amount of memory that STAR allocates for BAM sorting might not always suffice. The `--limitBAMsortRAM` parameter can be used to set this, but it's not available in the Galaxy wrapper. It might be nice to add this so (with a default 0 and buried in the advanced settings) for those circumstances when the default needs to be tweaked.\n\nFor reference, the error message produced when the default doesn't work is some variant of:\n\n    EXITING because of fatal ERROR: not enough memory for BAM sorting: \n    SOLUTION: re-run STAR with at least --limitBAMsortRAM 4815221017\n    Oct 10 14:22:48 ...... FATAL ERROR, exiting","files":null}]}